title: Divisors 2
text:
Let N be a positive integer and d(N) be the number of positive divisors of  N including 1 and N. Your task is to compute all N in [1, 106] for which d(N) > 3 and if M divides N then d(M) divides d(N) too.InputNone.OutputTo make the problem less output related write out only every 108-th of them, one per line.ExampleOutput:267
511
753
...
999579
999781
999977
